  "original_title": "\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dda \u0dc3\u0d82\u0da0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0d9a \u0db4\u0dc4\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd0\u0d82\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dbb",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Steps to increase tourist facilities in Yale",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ministry of Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation has taken many steps to increase the facilities provided to local and foreign tourists visiting Yala National Sanctuary.",
        "The Minister of Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera went on an observation tour to find out about the development of infrastructure in the Yala Sanctuary. Especially with the current economic collapse in the country, there is a reduction in the number of local and foreign tourists visiting Yala and other sanctuaries.",
        "Nevertheless, the minister mentioned that as the arrival of tourists to the country may increase again in the program of economic stability undertaken by the government, steps should be taken to increase the facilities provided to attract more of them to our country.",
        "Accordingly, the Minister observed that the construction work of the resting place currently being built by the Wildlife Department in the Yala Sanctuary has been stalled. The minister instructed the officials to take steps to resume the construction of the resting place.",
        "Currently, there is no designated place in the forest for the tourists who come inside the Yala sanctuary to get food and drink and provide other information and get water between 12 noon and 02 noon. Therefore, the minister instructed the officials to take steps to maintain this resting place as a green land with as much environmental appeal as possible.",
        "The minister also opened the new resort of Parana Pereyola. For this, the wildlife department has spent 100 million rupees. When local and foreign tourists stay here, it also has observatory facilities to see wild animals roaming around at night.",
        "The minister who participated in the event also inquired about the difficulties faced by the wildlife officials as well as the safari vehicle owners who transport tourists in getting fuel. Accordingly, he informed that necessary steps will be taken to provide the fuel they need from the Kataragama bus depot belonging to the Sri Lanka Transport Board.",
        "The minister who expressed his opinion said that when foreign tourists come to visit the Sri Lankan sanctuaries, an arrangement should be made to collect the relevant charges from them in dollars. The reason for the current crisis in the country is the lack of dollars. Therefore, the Minister also stated that it is his aim to take steps in the wildlife and forest resources conservation program to generate the necessary dollars for the country."
      ],
